metadata.name: PWTC #30
metadata.description:
PWTC (Play with tubes and circles) is an artistic exercise of creation by repetition. Composed with only 2 simple shapes and a limited color palette, the beauty of the patterns generated comes from the repetition and random ordering made possible by the junction of artistic thought in intersection with code.

#Main Features

* ORIENTATION â€“ 60% horizontal; 40% vertical
* TEXTURE â€“ 50% point; 30% scribble; 20% scratch
* GREY SCALE â€“ 5% chance
* INVERT â€“ 2,5% chance

#Royalties split: 20% for minters.

* Minters in the first stage of DA will receive a printed version *

metadata.name: SoulFish #182
metadata.description:
Named after the artist Wu Che-Yu, the soul fish was born in the void and crystallized from human emotions.

Fluttering silently and slowly, their bodies almost disappeared in the light of the deep sea.
The fish swims freely, and this is the happiness of the fish.
If we are not a fish, how do we know the joy of a fish?
How do we know that we do not know the joy of fish?
We will only learn about it when we come to the riverside.

Inspired by ZhuÄngzÇ: "The Debate on the Joy of Fish" c. 3rd century BC

Interactivities:
> Key S: Save
> Holding mouse in different directions: Swim 
> Click and let the fish touch the Bubbles
> Key B: Toggle border
> Key P: Pause

metadata.name: Uninhabitable #243
metadata.description:
Uninhabitable is a generative system built only from ellipses. The process of playing with different geometric and trigonometric disruptions gives rise to four different compositions which seek to evoque living constructions and environments. Besides the shape itself and its related distortion, the stroke weight of the lines plays a meaningful role in the piece. Following a discrete range [0.01,0.1,1] the weight reveals the process allowing the viewer to realize the trace of the huge amount of lines in each piece. This back and forth between scales and context is, while kind of stripping the code, part of my continuing interest on understanding the -usually- crazy paths of machines' way of thinking.

Press "h" to see it and high resolution and refresh to get back to the initial state. Press "h" to save it.

Uninhabitable is an original work by Iskra Velitchkova. 2021.

metadata.name: Cables and Clouds #84
metadata.description:
Capturing clouds... an old dream of mad scientist... coming true...
But wait... are they real clouds ? Maybe... maybe not...
Is it the real life ?
Is this just fantasy ?

Interaction.
Press h in live mode to list the possibilities.
Key 's'  : Save an image of the output at the current resolution
Key 1-9 : Change resolution
Key 'c' to change color palette
Key 'd' to toggle a special color mode to highlight the different components (and have the number of points used in your specific drawing).

Features.
18 different features displayed (format, color palettes, main elements characteristics, rare elements...).

metadata.name: Beam #300
metadata.description:
Warning: GPU intensive!

Editions tiers:
- 125 free
- 125 1tz
- 125 2tz
- 125 3tz
(each tier will be unlocked upon the previous one's completion)

Realistic simulation of an emissive beam traversing a piece of glass of different color and density placed on a metallic surface

(the preview has a resolution factor of 0.75 so it's a bit blurry, the generator has a default of 0.9)

hold the left mouse button and drag to rotate the view around the center

hover with your mouse to spawn some settings controls:
- Resolution (performance-heavy)
- Light bounces
- Frame Samples
- Screenshot Button (takes a screenshot...if it doesn't download, you should open the generator in a new tab)
- Rendering toggle (once you are satisfied with the output you can pause the rendering)

Created with threejs + three-gpu-pathtracer
